    "headline": "WinMagic Reveals What Comes After Passkeys: Identity Assurance That Lives Beyond Login",
    "summary": "Nearly half of Americans now use passkeys on at least one account, backed by Apple, Google, Microsoft, and the FIDO Alliance. The industry celebrates this shift from passwords to public-key cryptography as a phishing-resistant breakthrough. But while authentication improves, attackers have already moved on. They are no longer stealing passwords. They are targeting what happens after login: session tokens, cookies, and transactions that persist for hours with no continuous verification. Passkeys",
